# Patrón Container-Presenter

## Introducción

El patrón **Container-Presenter** (también conocido como Smart-Dumb Components) es una arquitectura que separa la lógica de negocio de la presentación visual.

### Beneficios

- **Separación de Responsabilidades:** Lógica vs Presentación
- **Testabilidad:** Componentes presentacionales son más fáciles de testear
- **Reutilización:** Presenters pueden usarse en diferentes contextos
- **Mantenibilidad:** Cambios en UI no afectan la lógica

## Container Components (Smart)

Los **containers** son componentes "inteligentes" que:

- Conectan con el **Store** (NgRx)
- Manejan **lógica de negocio**
- Hacen **llamadas a servicios**
- Gestionan **subscripciones**
- **No tienen estilos** complejos

### Ejemplo de Container

```typescript
// features/dashboard/containers/dashboard-container.component.ts
import { Component, OnInit } from '@angular/core';
import { Store } from '@ngrx/store';
import { Observable } from 'rxjs';
import * as DashboardActions from '../state/dashboard.actions';
import { selectUserData, selectAppointments, selectIsLoading } from '../state/dashboard.selectors';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-dashboard-container',
  template: `
    <app-dashboard-presenter
      [userData]="userData$ | async"
      [appointments]="appointments$ | async"
      [loading]="loading$ | async"
      (appointmentClick)="onAppointmentClick($event)"
      (refreshClick)="onRefresh()">
    </app-dashboard-presenter>
  `
})
export class DashboardContainerComponent implements OnInit {
  userData$: Observable<UserData>;
  appointments$: Observable<Appointment[]>;
  loading$: Observable<boolean>;

  constructor(private store: Store) {
    this.userData$ = this.store.select(selectUserData);
    this.appointments$ = this.store.select(selectAppointments);
    this.loading$ = this.store.select(selectIsLoading);
  }

  ngOnInit() {
    this.store.dispatch(DashboardActions.loadDashboard());
  }

  onAppointmentClick(appointmentId: string) {
    this.store.dispatch(DashboardActions.selectAppointment({ appointmentId }));
  }

  onRefresh() {
    this.store.dispatch(DashboardActions.refreshDashboard());
  }
}
```

## Presenter Components (Dumb)

Los **presenters** son componentes "tontos" que:

- Reciben datos por **@Input()**
- Emiten eventos por **@Output()**
- **No** acceden al Store
- **No** llaman servicios
- Se enfocan en la **presentación visual**
- Son **stateless** (sin estado interno complejo)

### Ejemplo de Presenter

```typescript
// features/dashboard/components/dashboard-presenter.component.ts
import { Component, Input, Output, EventEmitter, ChangeDetectionStrategy } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-dashboard-presenter',
  templateUrl: './dashboard-presenter.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./dashboard-presenter.component.scss'],
  changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush  // Optimización
})
export class DashboardPresenterComponent {
  @Input() userData: UserData | null = null;
  @Input() appointments: Appointment[] = [];
  @Input() loading = false;

  @Output() appointmentClick = new EventEmitter<string>();
  @Output() refreshClick = new EventEmitter<void>();

  onAppointmentClick(appointmentId: string) {
    this.appointmentClick.emit(appointmentId);
  }

  onRefresh() {
    this.refreshClick.emit();
  }
}
```

### Template del Presenter

```html
<!-- dashboard-presenter.component.html -->
<div class="dashboard">
  <app-loading *ngIf="loading"></app-loading>

  <div *ngIf="!loading" class="dashboard-content">
    <!-- User Info -->
    <div class="user-card" *ngIf="userData">
      <h2>Hola, {{ userData.name }}</h2>
      <p>Póliza: {{ userData.policyNumber }}</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Appointments List -->
    <div class="appointments-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h3>Próximas Citas</h3>
        <button (click)="onRefresh()" class="btn-refresh">
          Actualizar
        </button>
      </div>

      <div class="appointments-list">
        <app-appointment-card
          *ngFor="let appointment of appointments"
          [appointment]="appointment"
          (click)="onAppointmentClick(appointment.id)">
        </app-appointment-card>
      </div>

      <p *ngIf="appointments.length === 0" class="no-appointments">
        No tienes citas programadas
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Arquitectura Completa

```
User Interaction
      ↓
Presenter Component
      ↓ (emit event)
Container Component
      ↓ (dispatch action)
NgRx Store
      ↓ (effect)
API Service
      ↓ (response)
Reducer
      ↓ (new state)
Selector
      ↓ (derived data)
Container Component
      ↓ (pass data)
Presenter Component
      ↓
Re-render
```

## Estructura de Carpetas

```
features/dashboard/
├── containers/
│   └── dashboard-container.component.ts
├── components/
│   ├── dashboard-presenter.component.ts
│   ├── dashboard-presenter.component.html
│   └── dashboard-presenter.component.scss
├── state/
│   ├── dashboard.actions.ts
│   ├── dashboard.reducer.ts
│   ├── dashboard.effects.ts
│   └── dashboard.selectors.ts
└── dashboard.module.ts
```

## OnPush Change Detection

Los presenters deben usar **OnPush** para optimización:

```typescript
@Component({
  selector: 'app-user-profile-presenter',
  changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush
})
export class UserProfilePresenterComponent {
  @Input() user: User;

  // OnPush solo detecta cambios cuando:
  // 1. @Input() reference cambia
  // 2. Event ocurre en el template
  // 3. Se usa AsyncPipe
  // 4. Se llama manualmente ChangeDetectorRef.markForCheck()
}
```

### Inmutabilidad es Clave

```typescript
// ❌ Mal: Mutando objeto (OnPush no detecta)
this.userData.name = 'Nuevo nombre';

// ✅ Bien: Nuevo objeto (OnPush detecta)
this.userData = {
  ...this.userData,
  name: 'Nuevo nombre'
};
```

## Comunicación Entre Componentes

### De Container a Presenter (Input)

```typescript
// Container
userData$ = this.store.select(selectUserData);

// Template del Container
<app-presenter [userData]="userData$ | async"></app-presenter>
```

### De Presenter a Container (Output)

```typescript
// Presenter
@Output() saveClick = new EventEmitter<UserData>();

onSave() {
  this.saveClick.emit(this.userData);
}

// Template del Presenter
<button (click)="onSave()">Guardar</button>

// Container
<app-presenter (saveClick)="onSaveClick($event)"></app-presenter>

onSaveClick(userData: UserData) {
  this.store.dispatch(UserActions.saveUser({ userData }));
}
```

## Casos de Uso Reales

### Lista de Citas

```typescript
// Container
@Component({
  selector: 'app-appointments-container',
  template: `
    <app-appointments-list
      [appointments]="appointments$ | async"
      [loading]="loading$ | async"
      (cancel)="onCancel($event)"
      (reschedule)="onReschedule($event)">
    </app-appointments-list>
  `
})
export class AppointmentsContainerComponent {
  appointments$ = this.store.select(selectAppointments);
  loading$ = this.store.select(selectIsLoading);

  onCancel(appointmentId: string) {
    this.store.dispatch(AppointmentActions.cancel({ appointmentId }));
  }

  onReschedule(appointmentId: string) {
    this.router.navigate(['/appointments', appointmentId, 'reschedule']);
  }
}

// Presenter
@Component({
  selector: 'app-appointments-list',
  changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush
})
export class AppointmentsListComponent {
